National Security Advisor General Jim Jones recently completed a 5-day trip to Afghanistan and Pakistan. In Afghanistan, he met with Afghan, U.S., and ISAF leadership and visited various cities to assess the progress of the President's strategy in the region. In Pakistan, he met with President Zardari, Prime Minister Gilani, Foreign Minister Qureshi, and Chief of Army Staff Kayani to discuss mutual concerns, including development and security. General Jones also visited the Swat Valley and other areas in North West Frontier Province to commend the Pakistani Army and Frontier Corps on their successful security operations and acknowledge the sacrifices of Pakistan's security forces.